What?!

282
00:14:46,490 --> 00:14:48,320
Hey, Souma-chan!

283
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:51,030
<i>What's it being wrapped in?</i>

284
00:14:51,450 --> 00:14:52,740
<i>A crepe?</i>

285
00:14:52,740 --> 00:14:55,620
<i>Or a tortilla like they use for tacos?</i>

286
00:14:55,620 --> 00:14:57,000
<i>I have no idea.</i>

287
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:00,460
Well, well! If it isn't Mozuya-san!

288
00:15:00,460 --> 00:15:01,690
There's no need to skulk about.

289
00:15:01,690 --> 00:15:03,710
Why not line up with pride?

290
00:15:03,710 --> 00:15:07,710
H-How long have you been at this?

291
00:15:07,710 --> 00:15:08,550
Huh?

292
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:09,260
About three days.

293
00:15:09,260 --> 00:15:10,510
What?!

294
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,430
The hardware store provided
 the kitchen equipment.

295
00:15:13,430 --> 00:15:16,770
The sheet metal store crafted the Sumire Mark branding iron.

296
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:19,270
The grocer and butcher supplied
 us with the ingredients.

297
00:15:19,270 --> 00:15:22,730
And the printer made the flyers and the packaging.

298
00:15:22,980 --> 00:15:25,650
Everything was made here in the shopping district.

299
00:15:25,650 --> 00:15:27,030
In a single night.

300
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:33,240
Who'd like ice-cold beer to go
 with that karaage roll?!

301
00:15:33,570 --> 00:15:35,700
We're selling taiyaki at a discount right now!

302
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:38,160
We have cold ramune here!

303
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:40,620
Try our new dish!

304
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,040
Free dessert with each meal!

305
00:15:43,040 --> 00:15:44,960
Beer with this karaage? How sinful!

306
00:15:43,040 --> 00:15:44,960
It's like a festival!

307
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,550
Mister, please give me one of those.

308
00:15:46,550 --> 00:15:47,520
I'll have a beer.

309
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:49,130
<i>What in the world?</i>

310
00:15:49,130 --> 00:15:50,010
<i>With the karaage....</i>

311
00:15:50,470 --> 00:15:53,140
<i>No, with this brat at the center,</i>

312
00:15:53,140 --> 00:15:56,890
<i>the entire shopping district
 is coming back to life!</i>

313
00:15:58,180 --> 00:15:59,310
<i>I underestimated him.</i>

314
00:15:59,930 --> 00:16:02,310
<i>This brat's an extraordinary tactician!</i>

315
00:16:03,060 --> 00:16:06,770
<i>He laid siege to Mozuya in an instant,</i>

316
00:16:07,030 --> 00:16:11,240
<i>just like Sunomata Castle that
 Hideyoshi built in a single night!</i>

317
00:16:11,950 --> 00:16:14,240
Remember what you said, Mozuya-san?

318
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:18,950
A place with no competitiveness or
 creativity deserves to die out, right?

319
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:21,210
Well, this place has it.

320
00:16:21,210 --> 00:16:24,460
Our shopping district has what it takes!

321
00:16:26,210 --> 00:16:27,590
Quit your yapping!

322
00:16:27,590 --> 00:16:29,980
