BÃ¡nh xÃ¨o is a Vietnamese dish.

337
00:17:13,380 --> 00:17:18,970
A thin batter made of ingredients such as
rice flour, water, and coconut milk is cooked,

338
00:17:18,970 --> 00:17:21,820
then stuffed with ingredients such as pork, shrimp, and bean sprouts.

339
00:17:23,020 --> 00:17:24,600
<i>I get it now.</i>

340
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:26,020
<i>This is based on the idea</i>

341
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:30,110
<i>that piping hot rice and juicy karaage are a match made in heaven.</i>

342
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:33,530
<i>The pairing was reimagined,</i>

343
00:17:33,530 --> 00:17:39,870
<i>then further strengthened by improving its portability, taste, and visual impact!</i>

344
00:17:44,910 --> 00:17:47,460
<i>Students on their way home from club practice...</i>

345
00:17:47,460 --> 00:17:50,420
<i>Mothers rushing home to get dinner on the table...</i>

346
00:17:50,420 --> 00:17:52,380
<i>Commuters enjoying a break...</i>

347
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:56,590
<i>The hustle and bustle of
 the city are strangely relaxing.</i>

348
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:59,260
<i>This karaage...</i>

349
00:17:59,850 --> 00:18:02,560
<i>This ambiance...</i>

350
00:18:03,310 --> 00:18:09,350
<i>They invoke something far more brilliant than profits and returns.</i>

351
00:18:09,350 --> 00:18:11,070
<i>In this final match, it's the bottom of the ninth,</i>

352
00:18:11,070 --> 00:18:12,770
<i>with two outs and bases loaded.</i>

353
00:18:12,770 --> 00:18:14,990
<i>The pitcher winds up! Here's the pitch!</i>

354
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:29,420
<i>This... is the taste of youth!</i>

355
00:18:33,550 --> 00:18:34,590
Glad you liked it!

356
00:18:39,380 --> 00:18:42,390
Nikumi, you're really awesome!

357
00:18:42,850 --> 00:18:45,850
That marinade was super helpful.

358
00:18:45,850 --> 00:18:48,520
I hope you'll teach me
 a lot more from now on!

359
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:50,900
S-Sure, if I'm free.

360
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:53,610
<i>I envy Mito-san.</i>

361
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:58,780
<i>After tonight, I won't get to spend any more time with Yukihira-kun.</i>

362
00:18:59,110 --> 00:19:00,020
Kurase!

363
00:19:00,780 --> 00:19:04,120
Um, it's up to you, but...

364
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:05,990
Y-Yes?

365
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:08,620
Can you help Tomitaya out part-time?

366
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,000
What?!

367
00:19:10,330 --> 00:19:13,340
We just have to hang on till
 the karaage rolls stick, y'know?

368
00:19:13,790 --> 00:19:16,510
But it'll be a little shaky if we 
just rely on Tomita-san,

369
00:19:16,510 --> 00:19:18,590
and I can't be around most of the time.

370
00:19:18,590 --> 00:19:22,050
B-But I've never worked a job.

371
00:19:22,050 --> 00:19:23,600
There must be someone better suited toâ€”

372
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:24,720
Is there?

373
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:29,390
I thought I could depend on you,
 because I know you're a responsible person.

374
00:19:29,390 --> 00:19:30,230
What?

375
00:19:31,270 --> 00:19:36,020
In junior high, you'd work really late doing class council stuff.

376
00:19:36,020 --> 00:19:37,080
Even in elementary school,

377
00:19:37,080 --> 00:19:39,530
you never skipped watering
 the flowers when it was your turn.

378
00:19:40,740 --> 00:19:43,280
I'd feel a lot better if you were here.

379
00:19:45,410 --> 00:19:49,120
<i>I always thought that he was out of reach...</i>

380
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:52,120
<i>but he was paying attention to me?</i>

381
00:19:52,120 --> 00:19:53,480
Well, I won't force youâ€”

382
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:55,920
I'll... give it a try!

383
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:57,090
Really?

384
00:19:57,090 --> 00:19:58,260
You're a lifesaver!

385
00:19:58,710 --> 00:20:02,130
I'll come by sometimes to air out Yukihira,

386
00:20:02,130 --> 00:20:03,800
so you should drop by.

387
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:05,010
I'll cook for you.

388
00:20:05,010 --> 00:20:06,100
O-Okay!

389
00:20:06,390 --> 00:20:08,100
<i>Yay!</i>

390
00:20:08,770 --> 00:20:09,520
Huh?

391
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:10,850
What's the matter, Nikumi?

392
00:20:10,850 --> 00:20:12,640
Nothing...

393
00:20:13,520 --> 00:20:15,020
<i>It's great to be young.</i>

394
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:16,690
One here too.

395
00:20:16,690 --> 00:20:17,570
Me too.

396
00:20:17,110 --> 00:20:20,030
I've never felt so satisfied before!

397
00:20:17,570 --> 00:20:19,110
I want to try it.

398
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:22,900
So that's the Sumire Mark Karaage Roll.

399
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:24,660
What's the verdict?

400
00:20:24,950 --> 00:20:26,240
Here!

401
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:27,830
I give it twenty...

402
00:20:27,830 --> 00:20:30,000
out of ten!

403
00:22:00,420 --> 00:22:03,420
Sales have plummeted three days in a row.

404
00:22:04,070 --> 00:22:05,880
Well, Mozuya-san?

405
00:22:06,890 --> 00:22:08,840
What do you have to say for yourself?

406
00:22:11,010 --> 00:22:16,730
Well, so much for vacation.
 It was over in a flash.

407
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:22,150
Who the hell are you guys?

408
00:22:22,150 --> 00:22:24,380
Yukihira Souma, right?

409
00:22:24,380 --> 00:22:25,610
You're coming with us.

410
00:22:31,740 --> 00:22:32,910
There you are.

411
00:22:34,910 --> 00:22:36,330
And who're you?

412
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:41,790
The Sumire Mark Karaage Roll wasn't a bad idea.

413
00:22:42,920 --> 00:22:46,380
I'm the one who orchestrated
 Mozuya's Tokyo expansion.

414
00:22:46,970 --> 00:22:48,800
And not just Mozuya.

415
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:50,350
Since junior high,

416
00:22:50,350 --> 00:22:55,430
I've offered consulting services to over 500 businesses
 in the food industry and led each of them to success.

417
00:22:55,810 --> 00:22:59,520
I heard about how you revived
 the shopping district.

418
00:23:00,110 --> 00:23:02,730
Thanks to you, my record has been spoiled.

419
00:23:03,190 --> 00:23:05,520
So you want to beat me up now, is that it?

420
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:06,440
No.

421
00:23:06,820 --> 00:23:08,150
Come work for me.

422
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:12,060
I'll make sure you never go hungry.

423
00:23:12,530 --> 00:23:16,080
I already have a goal: 
to carry on my family restaurant.

424
00:23:16,830 --> 00:23:19,910
I have no plans to work for anyone else.

425
00:23:21,540 --> 00:23:24,130
To be honest, I didn't think
 you'd accept my offer.

426
00:23:24,130 --> 00:23:25,550
You're like everyone else.

427
00:23:25,880 --> 00:23:26,970
Huh?

428
00:23:26,970 --> 00:23:29,950
You're trapped in your own little world.

429
00:23:29,950 --> 00:23:33,300
As long as you can pretend to be a professional, you're satisfied.

430
00:23:33,890 --> 00:23:36,310
Your restaurant's small-time, isn't it?

431
00:23:36,310 --> 00:23:40,140
Is your ambition so limited because you were born into that kind of place?

432
00:23:40,480 --> 00:23:41,340
Well?

433
00:23:41,340 --> 00:23:43,060
You talk big,

434
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:45,690
but you're a chef too, aren't you?

435
00:23:45,690 --> 00:23:46,520
I am not.

436
00:23:47,320 --> 00:23:50,820
What I am is the one whom all the chefs obey.

437
00:23:51,410 --> 00:23:53,990
I've set my sights on an entirely different stage.

438
00:23:54,530 --> 00:23:55,700
Yukihira Souma,

439
00:23:56,410 --> 00:24:00,910
